14/04/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The Special Prosecution Office against Organised Crime has filed charges against alleged drug trafficker Darko Saric and 19 suspected members of his gang over their alleged involved in cocaine smuggling, Special Prosecutor Miljko Radisavljevic announced on Tuesday (April 13th).
They are suspected of organising drug trafficking from South America to Western Europe via Serbia.
Eleven of those accused are in custody, while Saric and the others are at large.
(Beta, Tanjug, Politika, RTS, B92, AFP - 13/04/10)
